romised me one night. I want you next to me tonight. We have the rest of our lives to be apart.', 16452, 0), (258689, 'She was seriously in love, but she never made demands.', 48, 0), (258690, 'Girls spilled drinks down their dresses and flicked their hair. Wishing anyone, maybe even you, would notice them... You were someone to me.', 6431, 0), (258691, 'You wanted a wife but I wasstill a girl.', 6431, 0), (258692, 'My Love wakes in a puddle of sunlight.Her hands asleep beside her.Her hair draped on the lawnlike a mantle of cloth.I give her my troth, for our love is wholeI sing her beauty in my soul', 587, 0), (258693, 'My words did not seem to reach her. Or, if they did, she was unable to grasp their meaning.', 48, 0), (258694, 'To her own heart, which was shaped exactly like a valentine, there came a winglike palpitation, a delicate exigency, and all the fragrance of all the flowery springtime love affairs that ever were seemed waiting for them in the whisky bottle. To mingle their pain their handshake had promised them, was to produce a separate entity, like a child that could shift for itself, and they scrambled hastily toward this profound and pastoral experience.', 44586, 0), (258695, 'I don''t know, it''s stupid being 20," she said. "I''m just not ready. It feels weird. Like somebody''s pushing me from behind.', 48, 0), (258696, 'But certainly not everyday you can find someone who wants to have a monogamous relationship', 303, 0), (258697, 'I give you," said Alexander, glancing at her, "what you need most from me.', 44587, 0), (258698, 'I worry about anything happening to you ... because I truly love you, every bit of you.', 44588, 0), (258699, 'Love is tranquility in the world.', 30849, 0), (258700, 'The endless thing in the world is Love.That is Beautiful.', 44589, 0);
